Storage: Persistent Volume (PV), Persistent Volume Claims (PV), StorageClasses, ConfigMaps.

If we need to map the container storage with our host(server) storage for the Persistent data storage in case of pod crashes so on auto healing our next container spin-up will have that particular data. so for this behaviour we need this Persistent Volume (PV) and Persistent Volume Claims

--------------------- Persistent Volume ------------------------

---> vim persistentVolume.yml
--->
kind: PersistentVolume
apiVersion: v1
metadata:
    name: local-pv
    namespace: nginx-dev
    labels:
        app: local
spec:
    capacity: 
        storage: 1Gi        # 1Gi = 1000MB
    accessModes:
        - ReadWriteOnce
    persistentVolumeReclaimPolicy: Retain  # means the 1Gi storage we allocate to our server will be retained
    storageClassName: local-storage  # means we are storing the data on our local machine similar we can store on pendrive, cloud storage etc.
    hostPath:
        path: /mnt/data

----

root@controlplane:~/k8s_cluster$ kubectl get pv
NAME       CAPACITY   ACCESS MODES   RECLAIM POLICY   STATUS      CLAIM   STORAGECLASS    VOLUMEATTRIBUTESCLASS   REASON   AGE
local-pv   1Gi        RWO            Retain           Available           local-storage   <unset>                          24s

----------------------------------------------------------------

NOTE :-  So the analogy is something like that we have created the persistentVolume on our local machine which is now available but someone need to claim that particular volume so that is your persistent volumen claim

------------------- Persistent Volume Claim ----------------------

---> vim persistentVolumeClaim.yml
--->
kind: PersistentVolumeClaim
apiVersion: v1
metadata:
    name: local-pvc
    namespace: nginx-dev
spec:
    accessModes:
        - ReadWriteOnce
    resources:
        requests:
            storage: 1Gi  # how much resource storage u want to claim 
    storageClassName: local-storage

---

Now u can see the persistent volume is claimed

. root@controlplane:~/k8s_cluster$ kubectl get pv
NAME       CAPACITY   ACCESS MODES   RECLAIM POLICY   STATUS   CLAIM               STORAGECLASS    VOLUMEATTRIBUTESCLASS   REASON   AGE
local-pv   1Gi        RWO            Retain           Bound    default/local-pvc   local-storage   <unset>                          14m

. root@controlplane:~/k8s_cluster$ kubectl get pvc
NAME        STATUS   VOLUME     CAPACITY   ACCESS MODES   STORAGECLASS    VOLUMEATTRIBUTESCLASS   AGE
local-pvc   Bound    local-pv   1Gi        RWO            local-storage   <unset>                 76s

----------------------------------------------------------------

- Now u can create the deployment.yml file and in which the data will not be deleted if the pod crashes or delete somehow.

---> vim deployment.yml
--->
kind: Deployment
apiVersion: apps/v1
metadata:
  name: nginx-deployment
  namespace: nginx-dev

spec:
  replicas: 2
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: nginx

  # Pod template
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: nginx

    spec:
      containers:
        - name: nginx
          image: nginx:latest
          ports:
            - containerPort: 80
          volumeMounts:  # nginx container path will be mount to one of the volumentMounts 
            - mountPath: /var/www/html  # nginx html file exist in this location where the nginx data will be stored
              name: nginx-local-pv  # this volumen name could be something 
      volumes:
        - name: nginx-local-pv  # this volumen name could be something
          persistentVolumeClaim:
            claimName: local-pvc

---

Note :- Whenever u got some trouble in pod u can do describe pods
. root@controlplane:~/k8s_cluster$ kubectl describe pod/nginx-deployment-7c5b9b4b7f-5tncb -n nginx-dev

Note :- u must also define the namespace in the persistentVolume and persistentVolumeClaim otherwise the storage will be allocated in the default namespace.

---------------------- Delete command for PV and PVC -------------------

- kubectl delete pvc/local-pvc
- kubectl delete pv/local-pv

------------------------------------------------------------------------

---------------------- Command for more details regarding pod -------------------

- kubectl get pods -n nginx-dev -o wide
NAME                                READY   STATUS    RESTARTS   AGE     IP           NODE                          NOMINATED NODE   READINESS GATES
